nemacs-next GUI v1
==================

Launch:

  apps/nemacs-next/frontends/gui/nemacs-next-gui

The current v1 route is a thin X11 terminal shim around the existing
nemacs-next M4 session frontend.  It opens a real X11 window with xterm,
honors DISPLAY values of the form :N, :N.S, host:N, and host:N.S, and passes
NEMACS_NEXT_GUI_WIDTH / NEMACS_NEXT_GUI_HEIGHT through to the M4 frame
snapshot request.

Why this route:

The raw-X11 Elisp spike proves that a pure-Elisp/AOT client can open a window,
load a core font, and blit glyphs.  For increments 1-2, the blocker for using
that path end-to-end is not drawing; it is live persistent-session I/O and
dynamic frame transport without adding a second app protocol or changing the
legacy GUI transport.  The v1 shim keeps editor semantics in
nemacs-next-session and gives users a real X11 window now.  The raw-X11/AOT
client remains the intended replacement for the xterm process once the frontend
has a narrow event/frame transport.

Works now:

- real X11 window on DISPLAY
- M4 frame rendering through the same snapshot path as the TUI
- toolbar row text from the protocol data
- printable keys, arrows, RET, DEL/Backspace, C-f/C-b/C-n/C-p, C-/ undo
- C-x C-f, C-x C-s, C-x C-c
- q exits when launched through this GUI wrapper

Deferred:

- raw-X11/AOT live renderer replacing the xterm shim
- mouse clicks and toolbar hit testing
- native menus
- OS clipboard integration
- OS IME integration beyond terminal text commit
